        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Evidence-Based Dentistry</h1>
            <p class="text-sm">Integrating clinical expertise, patient values, and the best available evidence</p>
        </div>
    </header>
main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What is Evidence-Based Dentistry?</h2>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
                Evidence-Based Dentistry (EBD) is the conscientious, explicit, and judicious use of current best evidence
                in making decisions about the care of individual patients. It integrates clinical expertise with the best
                available external clinical evidence from systematic research.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Core Principles of EBD</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                <li>Systematic assessment of relevant scientific evidence</li>
                <li>Clinical expertise of the practitioner</li>
                <li>Consideration of patient’s needs, values, and preferences</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Steps in Practicing EBD</h2>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2">
                <li>Formulate a clear clinical question</li>
                <li>Search for the best available evidence</li>
                <li>Critically appraise the evidence</li>
                <li>Apply the evidence in clinical practice</li>
                <li>Evaluate the outcome</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Practical Recommendations for Patients</h2>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
                Based on current scientific evidence and expert consensus, here are some evidence-based recommendations for optimal oral health:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-4 space-y-2">
                <li>Brush twice daily with fluoride toothpaste to reduce cavities and maintain healthy gums.</li>
                <li>Floss daily to remove plaque and food particles between teeth where a toothbrush can't reach.</li>
                <li>Visit your dentist every 6 months for check-ups and professional cleaning.</li>
                <li>Limit sugar intake, especially sugary snacks and drinks, to prevent tooth decay.</li>
                <li>Use a mouthguard if you grind your teeth at night or play contact sports.</li>
                <li>Ask your dentist about sealants for children’s molars to protect against decay.</li>
                <li>Quit smoking and avoid tobacco products, which are major risk factors for gum disease and oral cancer.</li>
                <li>Consider fluoride treatments if you are at higher risk for dental caries.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-8">
